<h1 class="reveal text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Research</h1>

<section class="reveal p-6 rounded-xl bg-space-900 border border-space-700/50 mb-8">
  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nebula-400 mb-4">Research Overview</h2>
  <p class="text-starlight-200 leading-relaxed mb-6">
    I investigate the light-scattering properties of cosmic dust and their impact
    on the observable universe. By combining computational modelling with
    polarimetric techniques, I study how tiny dust particles in comets, asteroids,
    and interstellar clouds influence planetary system formation and the evolution
    of life on Earth. My work spans:
  </p>
  <ul class="space-y-3 text-starlight-200">
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="text-comet-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#9733;</span>
      <span>Scattering behaviour of dust in comets and asteroids as they approach the Sun.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="text-nebula-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#9678;</span>
      <span>Polarisation properties of dust in dark clouds and star clusters.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="text-comet-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#9679;</span>
      <span>Correlation between polarisation maxima/minima and scattering parameters.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="text-rust-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#9671;</span>
      <span>Umov effect studies for silicate, organic, and carbon aggregates.</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

